overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by adding database storage for responses, an admin dashboard for
  data access, and an authentication system. The approach involved evaluating
  the existing codebase, creating a detailed implementation plan, and then
  executing it. Key decisions included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for
  data persistence and implementing a simple password-based authentication. The
  authentication system was initially built with custom session management but
  was later refactored to leverage Next.js middleware for a cleaner and simpler
  route protection. The implementation covered updating demographics, creating
  database schemas, developing API endpoints for data handling and CSV export,
  and building the admin dashboard. During the testing phase, the form
  submission flow was debugged to ensure data was correctly saved to the
  database. The outcome is a fully functional system with clear instructions for
  database setup and testing.
